96
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:18,160
Ask then.

97
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,500
Well...

98
00:06:21,140 --> 00:06:22,420
About what you said...

99
00:06:22,780 --> 00:06:25,000
Not all mothers care enough to think of their children's names.

100
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,180
What do you mean?

101
00:06:40,220 --> 00:06:41,080
My name is Tin.

102
00:06:42,780 --> 00:06:44,140
I know that.

103
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:46,060
Tin and your surname is something with Nan.

104
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:48,880
But...

105
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,980
I just want to know why you said that.

106
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,720
My brother's name is Tul.

107
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:56,900
Tin and Tul.

108
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:59,900
Both of your names are much cooler than ours.

109
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:03,840
The reason that my mom gave me that name

110
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:07,020
is because she wanted it to match with my brother's.

111
00:07:08,620 --> 00:07:09,380
She wants me to be good

112
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:11,320
and smart

113
00:07:12,260 --> 00:07:13,620
like my brother.

114
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,820
I'm the son that she doesn't want.

115
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:20,920
I'm just Tin

116
00:07:21,720 --> 00:07:23,960
who will always live in my brother's shadow.

117
00:07:25,620 --> 00:07:26,440
Tin...

118
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:28,680
I'm sorry.

119
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:32,700
I didn't know what you've been through.

120
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:34,880
I'm curious because I saw you're making weird face.

121
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:44,140
You believe me?

122
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:48,360
What do you mean?

123
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,620
Just a little bit of acting, and you already fall for that?

124
00:07:53,860 --> 00:07:54,500
You're stupid.

125
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:56,940
You asshole!

126
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,360
I was worried about you. You're an asshole.

127
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:05,540
Thank you.

128
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,580
For what?

129
00:08:10,020 --> 00:08:11,020
For worrying.

130
00:08:12,540 --> 00:08:13,520
Who's worried?

131
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,360
That person must be crazy.

132
00:08:24,260 --> 00:08:25,640
What if I tell you the truth.

133
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:27,380
Will you believe me?

134
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,960
I have to pee. I'll be right back.

135
00:08:39,220 --> 00:08:40,000
Tin.

136
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:43,020
You're his good friend, right?

137
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:48,160
Yes.

138
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:52,000
Can you look after him for me?

139
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:55,960
He is a little bit foolish and naive.

140
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:58,300
People often trick him.

141
00:08:58,900 --> 00:08:59,820
Is it that often?

142
00:09:00,580 --> 00:09:02,060
Very often.

143
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:04,800
When he was young,

144
00:09:05,180 --> 00:09:07,400
he was fooled into believing that he would get an extra point

145
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,940
if he could open a girl's skirt.

146
00:09:08,940 --> 00:09:10,360
Can believed that!

147
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,860
He opened my skirt.

148
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,740
I was crying so hard back then.

149
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,580
That's not it.

150
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,980
He was tricked to get rid of ant's nest.

151
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:24,460
He also went into a house because someone told him that the dog was abused.

152
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,300
He almost died.

153
00:09:26,760 --> 00:09:29,420
Imagine a Thai Bangkaew dog attacking a ten-year-old kid.

154
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:30,920
I don't want to think about it anymore.

155
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:34,400
What did Can do then?

156
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:36,620
What can he do?

157
00:09:37,820 --> 00:09:40,400
It doesn't matter how many times he got hurt.

158
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:42,540
He's always optimistic.

159
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,060
He never gets angry at anyone.

160
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:50,280
He truly believes in his friends.

161
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:54,260
Why are you telling me all this?

162
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,580
Because you're smart.

163
00:09:58,020 --> 00:09:59,820
I want you to teach him.

164
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,560
Thank you for telling me this.

165
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,700
Can I trust you?

166
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,480
Type, are you there already?

167
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:38,800
Wait for me. I'm coming.

168
00:10:39,260 --> 00:10:41,180
Come on. Wait for me.

169
00:10:41,660 --> 00:10:42,540
Alright.

170
00:10:59,460 --> 00:11:00,320
What are you doing here?

171
00:11:05,980 --> 00:11:08,340
Keng has been waiting for you for two hours already.

172
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:13,360
Techno.

173
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:17,260
Can I talk to you about...

174
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:19,000
that night?

175
00:11:19,460 --> 00:11:21,300
Shut up! Technic is still here!

176
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:26,200
Come on.

177
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:29,060
Brother.

178
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:31,220
Actually,

179
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:32,680
I know everything.

180
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:34,480
Huh?

181
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,140
I'm not joking.

182
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:42,000
But I don't want to interfere with this matter.

183
00:11:43,740 --> 00:11:44,840
You two should talk.

184
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:57,120
Techno.

185
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,480
What can I do

186
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,800
